<TITLE> Rain ruins Tigers' tour opener </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Colombo, June 22 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh's three-day tour opener against Sri Lanka A ended in a drab draw Friday with much of the match, including the final day, washed out in the Colts Cricket Stadium. Sri Lanka A scored 170 for four in 36.3 overs in their first innings before the rain forced a halt in play that did not resume. Bangladesh earlier declared their first innings at the overnight score of 245 for eight. Bangladesh seamer Syed Russel got the first wicket of Sri Lanka A when he had opener Michael Vandort with the team's score on 61. The Lankans put up 57 runs for the second wicket before spinner Abdur Razzak trapped opener Mahela Udawatte. 53, leg before. Razzak's spin partner Sakib Al Hasan trapped captain Thilan Samaraweera lbw for 30. Medium-pacer Mohammad Sharif took the the wicket of Jehan Mubarak (11) to leave Sri Lanka A at 161 for four. Prasanna Jayawardene was unbeaten on 31 and Thilina Kandamby on 1 when the match was over. bdnews
